gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Lakers 132, Raptors 131
gameRecap.excerpt: Anthony Davis leads the Lakers with a season-high 41 points (20 in the 4th), 11 rebounds and 6 assists as the Lakers defeat the Raptors, 132-131.  LeBron James adds 22 points, five rebounds and 12 assists in the victory, while Scottie Barnes leads the Raptors with 26 points and 6 assists in the losing effort.  Pascal Siakam (25 points, 10-17 FG), RJ Barrett (23 points, 10 rebounds, five assists) and Immanuel Quickley (21 points, five rebounds, five assists) added 69 more points with four Raptors starters putting up 20+ points. The Lakers improve to 19-19 on the season, while the Raptors fall to 15-22.
